title: Jonathan Joestar
bio: Jonathan Joestar (ジョナサン・ジョースター, Jonasan Jōsutā) is the main protagonist of the first part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Phantom Blood, and the first JoJo of the series. His legacy extends throughout almost the entirety of the first six parts of the series, with major characters such as Joseph Joestar and Jotaro Kujo being his descendants.

title: Will Anthonio Zeppeli
bio: Will Anthonio Zeppeli (ウィル・Ａ(アントニオ)・ツェペリ, Wiru Antonio Tseperi), also known as Baron Zeppeli (ツェペリ男爵, Tseperi Danshaku), is a primary ally featured in the first part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Phantom Blood.

bio: Robert E. O. Speedwagon (ロバート・E・O・スピードワゴン, Robāto Ī Ō Supīdowagon) is a primary ally featured in the 1st part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Phantom Blood. Formerly a Londoner thug residing in Ogre Street, Speedwagon befriends Jonathan Joestar and becomes a loyal ally to his cause.

title: Dio Brando
bio: Dio Brando (ディオ・ブランドー, Dio Burandō), later known simply as DIO (ＤＩＯ(ディオ)), is the main antagonist of the first and third parts of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Phantom Blood and Stardust Crusaders, as well as a posthumous primary antagonist in the sixth part, Stone Ocean. His influence is felt throughout all of the first six parts of the series, with major characters such as Giorno Giovanna and Enrico Pucci being directly connected to him.

bio: Joseph Joestar (ジョセフ・ジョースター, Josefu Jōsutā) is the main protagonist of the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency, and the second JoJo of the series. He also appears as a primary ally in Stardust Crusaders, and a secondary ally in Diamond is Unbreakable.

title: Messina
bio: Messina (メッシーナ, Messhīna) is a minor ally featured in the second part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Battle Tendency. As Lisa Lisa's servants and Ripple masters, he and Loggins train Joseph and Caesar Anthonio Zeppeli in the ways of the Ripple.

title: Loggins
bio: Loggins (ロギンズ, Roginzu) is a minor ally featured in the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency. As one of Lisa Lisa's servants and a fellow Ripple master, he personally trains Joseph after his first encounter with the Pillar Men.

title: Suzi Q
bio: Suzi Q (スージーQ, Sūjīkyū), later known as Suzi Q Joestar (スージーQ・ジョースター, Sūjīkyū Jōsutā), is a minor character featured in the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency, and then the third part, Stardust Crusaders. She is Lisa Lisa's servant, but a powerless human. Suzi Q becomes Joseph Joestar's love interest and later wife.

title: Kars
bio: Kars (カーズ, Kāzu) is the main antagonist of the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency, and the second main antagonist of the series.

title: Esidisi
bio: Esidisi (エシディシ, Eshidishi) is an antagonist featured in the second part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Battle Tendency. He is the second highest ranked Pillar Man after Kars and battles the Ripple users for the possession of the Red Stone of Aja.

title: Donovan
bio: Donovan (ドノヴァン, Donovan) is a minor antagonist featured in the second part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Battle Tendency. Donovan is a Nazi special force member sent to apprehend Joseph Joestar in the Mexican desert.

title: Wired Beck
bio: Wired Beck (鋼線(ワイアード)のベック, Waiādo no Bekku) is a minor antagonist featured in the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency, specifically in the "Climb Out of the Fortified Hotel" story arc.

title: Mark
bio: Mark (マルク, Maruku) is a tertiary ally featured in the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency. Mark is a German soldier and a friend of Caesar Zeppeli who participated in the effort of stopping the Pillar Men's awakening.

title: Mario Zeppeli
bio: Mario Zeppeli (マリオ ・ ツェペリ, Mario Tseperi) is a posthumous minor character featured in the 2nd part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Battle Tendency. The father of Caesar Anthonio Zeppeli, he was cooperating with Lisa Lisa in the fight against the Pillar Men.

title: Jotaro Kujo
bio: Jotaro Kujo (空条 承太郎 , Kūjō Jōtarō) is the main protagonist of the third part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Stardust Crusaders, and the third JoJo of the series. He also appears as a major ally in Diamond is Unbreakable and Stone Ocean, and makes a brief appearance in Vento Aureo. As a result of all his appearances, Jotaro is the most recurring JoJo protagonist of the series.

bio: Joseph Joestar (ジョセフ・ジョースター, Josefu Jōsutā) is the main protagonist of the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency, and the second JoJo of the series. He also appears as a primary ally in Stardust Crusaders, and a secondary ally in Diamond is Unbreakable.

title: Suzi Q
bio: Suzi Q (スージーQ, Sūjīkyū), later known as Suzi Q Joestar (スージーQ・ジョースター, Sūjīkyū Jōsutā), is a minor character featured in the second part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Battle Tendency, and then the third part, Stardust Crusaders. She is Lisa Lisa's servant, but a powerless human. Suzi Q becomes Joseph Joestar's love interest and later wife.

title: Dio Brando
bio: Dio Brando (ディオ・ブランドー, Dio Burandō), later known simply as DIO (ＤＩＯ(ディオ)), is the main antagonist of the first and third parts of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Phantom Blood and Stardust Crusaders, as well as a posthumous primary antagonist in the sixth part, Stone Ocean. His influence is felt throughout all of the first six parts of the series, with major characters such as Giorno Giovanna and Enrico Pucci being directly connected to him.

bio: Sherry Polnareff (シェリー・ポルナレフ, Sherī Porunarefu) is a minor character in the third part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Stardust Crusaders. Polnareff temporarily allies himself with DIO in order to find the man who killed her and get his revenge.

bio: Josuke Higashikata (東方 仗助, Higashikata Jōsuke) is the main protagonist of the fourth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Diamond is Unbreakable, and the fourth JoJo of the series. He is the illegitimate son of Joseph Joestar and Tomoko Higashikata.

title: Koichi Hirose

title: Rohan Kishibe
bio: Rohan Kishibe (岸辺 露伴, Kishibe Rohan) is a main ally featured in the fourth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Diamond is Unbreakable. First featured as an antagonist in the "Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House" story arc, he cooperates in the search for Yoshikage Kira.

title: Jotaro Kujo
bio: Jotaro Kujo (空条 承太郎 , Kūjō Jōtarō) is the main protagonist of the third part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Stardust Crusaders, and the third JoJo of the series. He also appears as a major ally in Diamond is Unbreakable and Stone Ocean, and makes a brief appearance in Vento Aureo. As a result of all his appearances, Jotaro is the most recurring JoJo protagonist of the series.

title: Jolyne Cujoh
bio: Jolyne Cujoh (空条 徐倫, Kūjō Jorīn) is the protagonist of the sixth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Stone Ocean, and the sixth JoJo of the series. She is the daughter of an American woman and Jotaro Kujo, the protagonist of Stardust Crusaders.

title: Ermes Costello
bio:
Ermes Costello (エルメェス・コステロ, Erumēsu Kosutero), is a major ally featured in the sixth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Stone Ocean.
Ermes is a woman voluntarily imprisoned in Green Dolphin Street Prison in order to seek revenge for her sister Gloria Costello's killer, Sports Maxx, and soon allies herself with Jolyne Cujoh in the hostile environment that the jail is. Thanks to a certain pendant, Ermes acquires her own Stand, Kiss.

title: Jotaro Kujo
bio: Jotaro Kujo (空条 承太郎 , Kūjō Jōtarō) is the main protagonist of the third part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Stardust Crusaders, and the third JoJo of the series. He also appears as a major ally in Diamond is Unbreakable and Stone Ocean, and makes a brief appearance in Vento Aureo. As a result of all his appearances, Jotaro is the most recurring JoJo protagonist of the series.

title: Josuke Higashikata (JoJolion)
bio: Josuke Higashikata (東方 定助, Higashikata Jōsuke) is the protagonist of the eighth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, JoJolion, and is the eighth JoJo of the series.

title: Yasuho Hirose

title: Rai Mamezuku
bio: Rai Mamezuku (豆銑 礼, Mamezuku Rai) is a major ally featured in the eighth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, JoJolion.

title: Norisuke Higashikata IV

title: Jobin Higashikata

title: Mitsuba Higashikata
bio: Mitsuba Higashikata (東方 密葉, Higashikata Mitsuba) is a secondary character featured in the eighth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, JoJolion. Gaining significance during the "Doctor Wu and Awaking 3 Leaves" story arc, she becomes a temporary ally to Yasuho Hirose.

title: Tsurugi Higashikata
bio: Tsurugi Higashikata (東方 つるぎ, Higashikata Tsurugi) is a side character featured in the 8th part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, JoJolion. Tsurugi cooperates with different factions during the course of the story.

title: Joshu Higashikata
bio: Joshu Higashikata (東方 常秀, Higashikata Jōshū) is a side character featured in the eighth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, JoJolion.

title: Hato Higashikata
bio: Hato Higashikata (東方 鳩, Higashikata Hato) is a side character featured in the eighth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, JoJolion. Introduced early in the story, she gains significance in the "Hato Brought Her Boyfriend Home" story arc and becomes a temporary ally in Walking Heart.

title: Daiya Higashikata
bio: Daiya Higashikata (東方 大弥, Higashikata Daiya) is a side character featured in the eighth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, JoJolion. Introduced as an antagonist in the "California King Bed" story arc, Daiya becomes a neutral character in subsequent arcs.

title: Kaato Higashikata
bio: Kaato Higashikata (東方 花都, Higashikata Kāto) is a tertiary character featured in the eighth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, JoJolion.

title: Kei Nijimura
bio: Kei Nijimura (虹村 京, Nijimura Kei) is a minor ally featured in the eighth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, JoJolion. Appearing as an antagonist in the "Paisley Park and Born This Way" story arc, she then becomes an ally in "The Wonder of You (The Miracle of Your Love)" story arc.

title: Yoshikage Kira (JoJolion)
bio: Yoshikage Kira (吉良 吉影, Kira Yoshikage) is a character featured in the eighth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, JoJolion. Introduced early in the story, Yoshikage gains significance in the "Vitamin C and Killer Queen" story arc.

title: Josefumi Kujo
bio: Josefumi Kujo (空条 仗世文, Kūjō Josefumi) is a character featured in the eighth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, JoJolion. Josefumi is alluded to in Love Love Deluxe, Part 2 but gains real significance in the "Vitamin C and Killer Queen" story arc.

title: Karera Sakunami
bio: Karera Sakunami (作並 カレラ, Sakunami Karera) is a side character featured in the eighth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, JoJolion, specifically the "Love Love Deluxe" story arc.

title: Tamaki Damo

Present in Ozon Baby's Pressure as a silhouette but fully introduced in the Doctor Wu and Awaking 3 Leaves story arc, he plays a major role in the Wonder of You (The Miracle Of Your Love).

title: Rohan Kishibe
bio: Rohan Kishibe (岸辺 露伴, Kishibe Rohan) is a main ally featured in the fourth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Diamond is Unbreakable. First featured as an antagonist in the "Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House" story arc, he cooperates in the search for Yoshikage Kira.

title: Yoshikage Kira
bio: Yoshikage Kira (吉良 吉影, Kira Yoshikage) is the main antagonist of the fourth part in the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Diamond is Unbreakable, and the third main antagonist of the series. He also appears as the protagonist of the short story Deadman's Questions.

title: Jolyne Cujoh
bio: Jolyne Cujoh (空条 徐倫, Kūjō Jorīn) is the protagonist of the sixth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Stone Ocean, and the sixth JoJo of the series. She is the daughter of an American woman and Jotaro Kujo, the protagonist of Stardust Crusaders.

title: Koichi Hirose
bio: Koichi Hirose (広瀬 康一, Hirose Kōichi) is the deuteragonist of the fourth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Diamond is Unbreakable. He also appears briefly as a minor ally in the fifth part, Vento Aureo, assisting Giorno Giovanna in the fight against Polpo's Stand, Black Sabbath.

title: Okuyasu Nijimura
bio: Okuyasu Nijimura (虹村 億泰, Nijimura Okuyasu) is a main ally featured in the fourth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Diamond is Unbreakable.

title: Josuke Higashikata
bio: Josuke Higashikata (東方 仗助, Higashikata Jōsuke) is the main protagonist of the fourth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Diamond is Unbreakable, and the fourth JoJo of the series. He is the illegitimate son of Joseph Joestar and Tomoko Higashikata.

title: Tamami Kobayashi
bio: Tamami Kobayashi (小林 玉美, Kobayashi Tamami) is a side character featured in the 4th part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Diamond is Unbreakable, introduced in the "Koichi Hirose (Echoes)" story arc.

title: Akira Otoishi
bio: Akira Otoishi (音石 明, Otoishi Akira) is an antagonist featured in the fourth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Diamond is Unbreakable, specifically in the "Red Hot Chili Pepper" story arc.

title: Mikitaka Hazekura
bio: Mikitaka Hazekura (支倉 未起隆, Hazekura Mikitaka), also self-proclaimed as Nu Mikitakazo Nshi (ヌ・ミキタカゾ・ンシ), is an ally featured in the 4th part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Diamond is Unbreakable, specifically in the "I'm an Alien" and "Let's Live on a Transmission Tower" story arcs.

title: Tonio Trussardi
bio: Antonio "Tonio" Trussardi (トニオ・トラサルディー, Tonio Torasarudī) is a minor character featured featured in the 4th part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, Diamond is Unbreakable, introduced in the "Let's Go Eat Some Italian" story arc. He also appears in the sixth episode of Thus Spoke Kishibe Rohan.

title: Yukako Yamagishi
bio: Yukako Yamagishi (山岸 由花子, Yamagishi Yukako) is a side character featured in the fourth part of the JoJo's Bizarre Adventure series, Diamond is Unbreakable. Introduced as a minor antagonist in the "Yukako Yamagishi Falls In Love" story arc, she becomes a neutral character in the "Yukako Yamagishi Dreams of Cinderella" arc.
